Long-Run Economic Growth

Path to economic growth is different for different economies

!!! Energing countries growth due to capital is not sustainable long term, 
!!! while TFP can  !!!

= Evidence - Growth accounting =
Look at the growth history

Y = A*K^alpha*L^(1-alpha)       <-- very special equation (Cobb-Douglas production function)
                                <-- K is capital, L is labor, A is total factor of production
                                <-- alpha is just a number with value between 0 and 1 (eg alpha = 0.25) 
!!! alpha to replicate what we see in the real world

!!! They are a lot of others production function that can be used, but this one is very practical as we will see later!

1/ Consistent with diminishing marginal productivity (will trend to a plateau)
2/ Consistent with return to scale, CRS
    - K = 1 , L = 1 ==> output = X
    - K = 2 , L = 2 ==> output = 2 * X
    - K = 3 , L = 3 ==> output = 3 * X


